      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 52: The fallback timer clears the filter after 5 seconds regardless of whether the user has changed the search/filter since `setFilterAndSelect()` was called. If a URI-triggered search starts and the user types a different query before the timeout, their active search will be cleared unexpectedly. Store the pending URI filter and only clear if the current filter still matches that pending value, or cancel the timer on manual filter changes.\n```suggestion\nconnect(\u0026searchFallbackTimer_, \u0026QTimer::timeout, this, [this, pending \u003d filterString]() {\n    if (currentFilter_ \u003d\u003d pending)\n        setFilter({});\n});\n```",
