      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 97: Adding `pluginData` to the serialized `SwarmMessage` structure changes the D-Bus signature unconditionally. This will break compatibility whenever the client and daemon are not rebuilt/deployed together, because older daemons will emit one fewer field and deserialization will fail or misread the message. Please either gate this by daemon API/version negotiation or introduce a backward-compatible message type/path so older peers continue to work.\n```suggestion\n// Keep the existing SwarmMessage D-Bus layout stable, or only read/write\n// pluginData after confirming the daemon exposes the newer conversation API.\n```",
      "revId": "e7dff30a81ba4c4e86a11b8b8a6cc5f41d9323b4",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
